ng degrees and the fields of concentration that are available to you, but also the outstanding faculty and facilities to make your learning experience memorable and productive. Dean Costas Tsatsoulis Biomedical Engineering, Computer science, computer engineering, information technology, electrical engineering, materials science and engineering, mechanical and energy engineering, and our Technology programs in construction engineering, electrical engineering, and mechanical engineering – these degree programs prepare you to compete in today's global market. A course of study in engineering will equip you with life-long learning skills and provide you research opportunities in emerging technologies, nanoscience and microscience technology, and computer science and technology. I am looking forward to developing new departments and programs; supporting the existing ones; growing our research and graduate programs; and continuing our service to our students, the state of Texas, and the Nation. The College of Engineering at UNT’s Discovery Park is growing at a rapid pace, and I am excited about the opportunity to help lead it forward. About Us Accreditation Staff Directory Advisory Board Corporate Partners IT Services About Discovery Park Take a Tour Maps & Directions History of the College Strategic Plan Organizational Chart Alumni Videos Photo Gallery Contact Us: UNT College of Engineering 3940 N Elm Street Denton, TX 76207-7102 USA Voice: 940-565-4300 Fax: 940-369-8570 Visit Us: UNT Discovery Park http://engineering.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions about website technical issues? Please contact us. Have other questions? Please visit our contact page. UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on May 5, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness 